First Lady Michelle Obama will be speaking at the American Magazine Media Conference on February 2nd. She will be joined by actresses Lena Dunham and Julianne Moore, as well as editor-in-chief of MORE Magazine, Lesley Jane Seymour. The panel discussion, titled "Media with Purpose," will focus on the power of the media industry to raise awareness for important issues, such as adolescent girls' education worldwide. The event aims to support the Let Girls Learn initiative, which is dedicated to expanding access to education for adolescent girls around the world. The conference is hosted by the Association of Magazine Media (MPA), which represents 200 domestic, associate, and international members in advocating for the magazine media industry.